<p>“I am looking for friends. What does that mean – tame?”</p>

<p>“It is an act too often neglected,” said the fox. “It means to establish ties.”</p>

<p>“To establish ties?”</p>

<h2 id="just-that-said-the-fox-to-me-you-are-still-nothing-more-than-a-little-boy-who-is-just-like-a-hundred-thousand-other-little-boys-and-i-have-no-need-of-you-and-you-on-your-part-have-no-need-of-me-to-you-i-am-nothing-more-than-a-fox-like-a-hundred-thousand-other-foxes-but-if-you-tame-me-then-we-shall-need-each-other-to-me-you-will-be-unique-in-all-the-world-to-you-i-shall-be-unique-in-all-the-world">“Just that,” said the fox. “To me, you are still nothing more than a little boy who is just like a hundred thousand other little boys. And I have no need of you. And you, on your part, have no need of me. To you I am nothing more than a fox like a hundred thousand other foxes. But if you tame me, then we shall need each other. To me, you will be unique in all the world. To you, I shall be unique in all the world….”</h2>

